author: cmpilato
msg: Locking branch: Ensure that svn_fs_attach_lock() implementations first
canonicalize the FS path stored in that lock.
* subversion/include/svn_fs.h
(svn_fs_lock): Update docstring to warn callers that the lock they
send in might not be the exact lock data used (because of the path
canonicalization stuffs).
* subversion/libsvn_fs_fs/lock.c
(svn_fs_fs__attach_lock): Canonicalize the input lock's path member.
* subversion/libsvn_fs_base/lock.c
(txn_body_attach_lock): Canonicalize the input lock's path member.
Also, lose an out-of-date (and unused) node-kind kludge.

author: cmpilato
msg: Locking branch: Expand testing of the svn_fs_get_locks() interface,
adding a little framework to facilitate further expansion.
* subversion/tests/libsvn_fs/locks-test.c
(struct get_locks_baton_t, get_locks_callback, make_get_locks_baton,
verify_matching_lock_paths): New svn_fs_get_locks() validation helpers.
(get_locks): Really flesh out this locks more paths and then query
various subsets, validating with our new coolio validation
functions.
(directory_locks_kinda): New test for deep (though non-existant) paths.
(test_funcs): Reference new directory_locks_kinda() test.
